        <div class="row"><div class="column vcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Tue, 06 Aug 2024 02:17:11 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Tue, 06 Aug 2024 02:17:11 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="SARAH PARVINI, Associated Press, NewsNation">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/06/elon-musk-sues-openai-renewing-claims-chatgpt-maker-put-profits-before-the-benefit-of-humanity.webp" alt="Elon Musk sues OpenAI, renewing claims ChatGPT-maker put profits before 'the benefit of humanity'"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Elon Musk sues OpenAI, renewing claims ChatGPT-maker put profits before 'the benefit of humanity'</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      LOS ANGELES (AP) — Elon Musk filed a lawsuit on Monday against OpenAI and two of its founders, Sam Altman and Greg Brockman, renewing claims that the ChatGPT-maker betrayed its founding aims of benefiting the public good rather than pursuing profits.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/06/elon-musk-sues-openai-renewing-claims-chatgpt-maker-put-profits-before-the-benefit-of-humanity/"  >(SARAH PARVINI, Associated Press, NewsNation)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div><div class="column text"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Fri, 02 Aug 2024 19:12:35 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Fri, 02 Aug 2024 19:12:35 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="HALELUYA HADERO, Associated Press, NewsNation">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/02/justice-department-sues-tiktok-accusing-the-company-of-violating-a-childrens-online-privacy-law.webp" alt="Justice Department sues TikTok, accusing the company of illegally collecting children's data"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Justice Department sues TikTok, accusing the company of illegally collecting children's data</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      The Justice Department sued TikTok on Friday, accusing the company of violating children’s online privacy law and running afoul of a settlement it had reached with another federal agency. The complaint, filed together with the Federal Trade Commission in a California federal court, comes as the U.S.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/02/justice-department-sues-tiktok-accusing-the-company-of-violating-a-childrens-online-privacy-law/"  >(HALELUYA HADERO, Associated Press, NewsNation)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 01 Aug 2024 10:31:00 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 01 Aug 2024 10:31:00 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Network World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/01/mitiga-zeros-in-on-cloud-and-saas-security.webp" alt="Mitiga zeros in on cloud and SaaS security"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Mitiga zeros in on cloud and SaaS security</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Mitiga is one of Network World’s 7 network security startups to watch for 2024. Its cloud-native security platform combines cloud threat detection and incident response.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/01/mitiga-zeros-in-on-cloud-and-saas-security/"  >(Network World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
