      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/07/full-stack-development-with-java-react-and-spring-boot-part-3.webp" alt="Full-stack development with Java, React, and Spring Boot, Part 3"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Full-stack development with Java, React, and Spring Boot, Part 3</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      In the first part of this tutorial, we created a Todo application with a React front end and a Spring Boot back end. In the second part, we added a local MongoDB instance for storage.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/07/full-stack-development-with-java-react-and-spring-boot-part-3/"  >(Info World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div><div class="column hcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Wed, 07 Aug 2024 09:49:41 +0000">
